<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What does the Bible say about fear and anxiety?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "2 Timothy 1:7 says God has not given us a spirit of fear, but of power, love, and a sound mind. Scripture consistently reminds believers that fear is not their portion — God's presence and promises overcome anxiety."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What does the Bible say about shame and guilt?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Romans 8:1 declares there is no condemnation for those in Christ Jesus. Scripture teaches that shame is broken at the cross. Through Jesus, believers receive forgiveness, righteousness, and a new identity — fully accepted, fully loved."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What does God say when I feel like a failure?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Philippians 1:6 promises that God who began a good work in you will complete it. Scripture teaches that failure does not define you — God's grace and faithfulness do. You are still His workmanship."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What Bible verses help with overthinking and worry?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Philippians 4:6-7 instructs believers not to be anxious, but to bring everything to God in prayer. Scripture promises God's peace will guard your mind. Casting your cares on Him is the antidote to overthinking."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What does the Bible say about loneliness?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Hebrews 13:5 says God will never leave you nor forsake you. Scripture promises God's constant presence even when you feel alone. The Holy Spirit dwells within every believer — you are never truly forsaken."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What does God say about my purpose?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Jeremiah 29:11 declares God has plans for you — plans for hope and a future. Scripture confirms you were created with intention. Your life carries divine purpose, designed by God before you were born."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What Bible verses speak to doubt and unbelief?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Mark 9:24 records a father crying out, 'I believe; help my unbelief.' Scripture honors honest doubt brought to God. Faith grows through wrestling, not avoiding. God meets you in the questions, not just the answers."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What does the Bible say about anger and bitterness?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Ephesians 4:31-32 instructs believers to release bitterness and forgive as Christ forgave. Scripture teaches that holding anger gives the enemy ground. Forgiveness is not weakness — it is freedom and obedience to God."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What does God say about financial stress?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Philippians 4:19 promises God will supply all your needs according to His riches in glory. Scripture teaches that God is provider. Trust in His faithfulness, not the size of your account, brings true peace."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What does the Bible say when I feel unworthy?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Ephesians 2:10 says you are God's workmanship, created for good works. Scripture declares your worth is not earned — it is given. You are loved, chosen, and called by the Creator of the universe."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What Bible verses help with grief and loss?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Psalm 34:18 says the Lord is close to the brokenhearted. Scripture honors grief as a sacred space where God draws nearest. Revelation 21:4 promises a day when He will wipe away every tear."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What does God say about depression and hopelessness?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Psalm 42:11 asks the soul why it is downcast and answers — hope in God. Scripture acknowledges deep sorrow while pointing to God as the lifter of your head. You are seen. You are not alone."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What does the Bible say about suicidal thoughts?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Your life is sacred and known by God. Psalm 139 declares you were fearfully and wonderfully made. If you are in crisis, please call or text 988 (Suicide and Crisis Lifeline) immediately. You are loved."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What Bible verses speak to spiritual dryness?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Psalm 63:1 expresses thirst for God in a dry land. Scripture teaches that seasons of dryness are not abandonment — they are invitations to deeper hunger. God meets the seeking heart with refreshing presence."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What does the Bible say about my identity in Christ?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "2 Corinthians 5:17 declares you are a new creation in Christ — the old has passed away. Scripture teaches your identity is not your past, your feelings, or your circumstances. You are who God says you are."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What Bible verse helps when you feel worthless?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Psalm 139:14 says you are fearfully and wonderfully made. Romans 8:38-39 says nothing can separate you from God's love. Declare and Believe finds the exact Scripture for what you're carrying right now."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What Bible verse helps with anxiety at night?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Philippians 4:6-7, Isaiah 41:10, and 2 Timothy 1:7 speak directly to fear and anxiety. Declare and Believe pairs these with personalized declarations you can speak over yourself right now."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How do I renew my mind with Scripture?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Romans 12:2 says be transformed by the renewing of your mind. Declare and Believe makes this practical — describe your struggle, receive the exact Scripture that speaks to it, and speak it over yourself as a declaration."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Is there a Christian app for when you feel hopeless?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Declare and Believe is a free Christian web app built for exactly that moment. Describe what you're battling and receive personalized Bible verses, prayer, and identity declarations rooted in God's Word."
      }
    }
  ]
}
</script>

